  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_0' aria-label=\" Satheesh V.K. versus The Federal Bank Ltd. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('0','2025','2025_9_1255_1272','2025INSC1140'); ><font size='4'> <strong>SATHEESH V.K.<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>THE FEDERAL BANK LTD. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 9 S.C.R. 1255</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 1140</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010008842025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : DIPANKAR DATTA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, K.V. VISWANATHAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Issue arose as regards the maintainability of the second SLP challenging the same order where the first SLP was withdrawn without leave to re-approach. Headnotes&dagger; Constitution of India &ndash; Art.136 &ndash; Maintainability of the second Special Leave Petition, when liberty &ndash; Appellant defaulted in his obligation to repay loan to the respondent-Bank &ndash; Respondent classified the loan account as &lsquo;Non-Performing Asset&rsquo; and initiated measures u/s.13(4) of the SARFAESI Act &ndash; Appellant filed writ petition, which was disposed of by the<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 23-09-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 11752/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Dismissed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('0','2025','2025_9_1255_1272','2025INSC1140','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a h